 issues could arise since engine 5.9 expects API 5.9, even though it may not affect most methods. The `ClassTemplateInvocationContextProvider` might be unknown to engine 5.9, but the test method should run normally if the class has the right extensions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JUnit versions**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the compatibility of API 6 with engine 5.9. The extension class has the same fully qualified name (FQN), but I'm not sure if engine 5.9 will fully support API 6, even though it might work. Ideally, upgrading everything to JUnit 6 would be preferable for Spring Test 7. However, the TCK plugin might still be at version 5.9, leading to potential dependency conflicts. It seems this is manageable for now, but I’ll need to keep an eye on it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating classpath scanning**\\n\\nI'm considering the job of TestClassScanner, which does open-ended classpath scanning for class definitions. With a native image, it might not find classes not known at build time. However, all classes are known at build in our test. The scanner scans the filesystem, while JUnit uses Class.forName to load classes by name. In a native context, if a class isn’t in the image, that could lead to an error, but all test classes are likely included.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering error handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether we should add a catch statement. It seems like if we catch it, then in native it passes when failure is unsupported. But dynamic access coverage in agent JVM still records, so we need to be mindful of that. I believe it should only apply for Error, not Exception. I'll also need to look into importing `org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport`, and maybe check existing tests to see how they handle this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pM7YAebKPQvVOks94f31Croi|fc_059c612d6c87edb9016a28fb12d0e08190b5d51cf81adf4c37", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError\" tests/src -n | head -20", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 451, "output": 1315, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43238, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781070579524, "responseId": "resp_059c612d6c87edb9016a28faf41c908190b77d07b3d8b4c090"}}
